`IFormFile` buffers the entire body into memory — that's why it OOMs. Instead, read the raw multipart stream section-by-section using `Microsoft.AspNetCore.WebUtilities.MultipartReader` and copy each file section directly to a `FileStream`.

**Key changes needed:**

### 1. Raise the request-size limits

```csharp
// Program.cs
builder.WebHost.ConfigureKestrel(o =>
    o.Limits.MaxRequestBodySize = 2L * 1024 * 1024 * 1024); // 2 GB
```

### 2. Stream the upload to disk (no buffering)

```csharp
app.MapPost("/upload", async (HttpRequest request) =>
{
    if (!request.HasFormContentType ||
        !MediaTypeHeaderValue.TryParse(request.ContentType, out var mt) ||
        string.IsNullOrEmpty(mt.Boundary.Value))
    {
        return Results.BadRequest("Expected a multipart/form-data request.");
    }

    var boundary = HeaderUtilities.RemoveQuotes(mt.Boundary.Value).Value!;
    var reader   = new MultipartReader(boundary, request.Body);

    MultipartSection? section;
    while ((section = await reader.ReadNextSectionAsync()) is not null)
    {
        if (!ContentDispositionHeaderValue.TryParse(
                section.ContentDisposition, out var cd) ||
            !cd.IsFileDisposition())
        {
            continue;                       // skip non-file fields
        }

        var trustedName = Path.GetRandomFileName();      // never trust the client name
        var savePath    = Path.Combine("/tmp/uploads", trustedName);

        await using var fs = new FileStream(
            savePath, FileMode.Create, FileAccess.Write,
            FileShare.None, bufferSize: 81920);          // 80 KB copy buffer

        await section.Body.CopyToAsync(fs);
    }

    return Results.Ok("Upload complete.");
})
.DisableAntiforgery();                     // needed for minimal-API form posts
```

### 3. Disable form-value limits on that endpoint

```csharp
// Apply via attribute or filter — default form limits (256 MB) would reject 2 GB
.WithMetadata(new RequestFormLimitsAttribute
{
    MultipartBodyLengthLimit = 2L * 1024 * 1024 * 1024
});
```

### Why this works

| | `IFormFile` | `MultipartReader` |
|---|---|---|
| Memory | Entire file buffered | Only the 80 KB copy buffer |
| Max practical size | ~few hundred MB | Limited only by disk space |
| API surface | Model-binding magic | Manual but full control |

### Don't forget

- **Validate content** — check file signatures/magic bytes, not just the extension.
- **Limit per-section size** — track bytes copied and abort if a section exceeds your cap.
- **Antivirus / scanning** — scan the saved file before promoting it out of the temp directory.
- **`[RequestSizeLimit]`** also works per-endpoint if you prefer attributes over global Kestrel config.
